# Internal operations runbook (release pipeline, rollback procedures,
# migration policy, infrastructure detail). This repo is public, so any
# operator-facing documentation that maps internal infrastructure must
# live here, untracked, rather than in the public README.
docs/

# Per-release user-facing note drafts. `publish-release.sh` (Step A and
# --publish-manifest) auto-consumes .release-notes-<version>.md into the GitHub
# Release body and latest.json. They're local authoring scratch — the published
# copy lives on the GitHub Release page and in latest.json, so keep them out of
# this public repo's history.
.release-notes-*.md
